/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1110620/extras/dcef05aaf07cc95bfb80c1c32d1813d2.mp4?t=1762594579\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The difficulty builds over  time. Use everything you've learned to beat the challenging end game!</p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Play On Steam Deck!</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1110620/extras/a7f35cef30ba15f31665b4ff4ee30acc.avif?t=1762594579\" width=600 height=336 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >I test every build on Steam Deck!</p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Aspect Ratios</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The game is currently letter-boxed on non 16:9 aspect ratio monitors. It's tricky to get this right for a 2D game--if we just allow arbitrary aspect ratios, then the camera will point outside the level bounds, or reveal secrets or puzzle elements you're not supposed to see yet. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >I'm not super happy about that. If the game does well enough I may be able to create a patch down the line where I do a pass over each puzzle and make custom camera frames for a few more common aspect ratios, but I can't make any promises right now! </p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Join My Discord</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >If you have feedback or just need a hint, the quickest way to reach me is our Discord, linked in the post on the forums.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Future games and beta testing opportunities are announced there, and it's a great place to chat with other players. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >- Mason</p>",
